html(lang='en', xmlns='http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml')
  head
    
    title Nav

    include header



  body

    include _nav


    .row

        div.col-12

          h1.divide-section Nav
          p.info Defines different styles for list navigations.
          h2 Usage
          p
            | To apply this component, add the 
            code .nav
            |  class to an 
            code= "<ul>"
            |  element. Use 
            code= "<a>"
            |  elements as menu items within the list. To apply an active state to a menu item, just add the 
            code .active
            |  class.
          
          .preview-box
            .width-per-33
              ul.nav.nav-side
                li.active
                  a(href='#') Active
                li
                  a(href='#') Item
                li
                  a(href='#') Item
          
          p
            span.badge.badge-info NOTE
            | By default, the nav has no styling. That's why it is important to add a 
            | modifier class to give it some styling. In our examples we used the 
            code .nav-side
            |  class.
          
            
          hr
          
          h3 Nested navs
          p
            | You can easily add any number of 
            code= "<ul>"
            |  elements to your nav.
          
          table.table.rounded
            thead
              tr
                th Class
                th Description
            tbody
              tr
                td
                  code .nav-sub
                td
                  | Add this class to the first nested 
                  code= "<ul>"
                  |  for optimized spacing.
              tr
                td
                  code .parent
                td Add this class to indicate a parent menu item.
              tr
                td
                  code .nav-parent-icon
                td Add this class to the nav to add icons, indicating parent items.
          

          .preview-box
            .width-per-33
              ul.nav.nav-side.nav-parent-icon
                li.active
                  a(href='') Active
                li
                  a(href='#') 
                     i.i-arrow-up
                     | Parent
                  ul.nav-sub
                    li
                      a(href='') Sub item
                    li
                      a(href='') Sub item
                      ul
                        li
                          a(href='') Sub item
                        li
                          a(href='') Sub item
          
          hr

          h3 Accordion
          p
            | By default child menu items are always visible. To apply the accordion effect, 
            | just add the 
            code data-nav
            |  attribute to the main 
            code= "<ul>"
            |  . When clicking on a parent item, an open one will close, allowing only one 
            |  open nested list at a time. To avoid this behavior, just append 
            code {multiple:true}
            |  to the data attribute.

          .preview-box
            .row
              .width-per-50
                p
                  code data-nav
                ul.nav.nav-side.nav-parent-icon.w-66(data-nav='')
                  li.active
                    a(href='') Active
                  li
                    a(href='') Item
                  li.parent
                    a(href='#') Parent
                    div(style='overflow: hidden; height: 0; position: relative;')
                      ul.nav-sub
                        li
                          a(href='') Sub item
                        li
                          a(href='') Sub item
                          ul
                            li
                              a(href='') Sub item
                            li
                              a(href='') Sub item
                  li.parent
                    a(href='#') Parent
                    div(style='overflow: hidden; height: 0; position: relative;')
                      ul.nav-sub
                        li
                          a(href='') Sub item
                        li
                          a(href='') Sub item
              .width-per-50
                p
                  code data-nav="{multiple:true}"
                ul.nav.nav-side.nav-parent-icon.w-66(data-nav='{multiple:true}')
                  li.active
                    a(href='') Active
                  li
                    a(href='') Item
                  li.parent
                    a(href='#') Parent
                    div(style='overflow: hidden; height: 0; position: relative;')
                      ul.nav-sub
                        li
                          a(href='') Sub item
                        li
                          a(href='') Sub item
                          ul
                            li
                              a(href='') Sub item
                            li
                              a(href='') Sub item
                  li.parent
                    a(href='#') Parent
                    div(style='overflow: hidden; height: 0; position: relative;')
                      ul.nav-sub
                        li
                          a(href='') Sub item
                        li
                          a(href='') Sub item
          
                
          hr
          
          h3 Header and divider
          p
            | Add one of the following classes to a list item to create a header 
            |  or a divider between items.
          table.table
            thead
              tr
                th Class
                th Description
            tbody
              tr
                td
                  code .nav-header
                td
                  | Add this class to a 
                  code= "<li>"
                  |  element to create a header.
              tr
                td
                  code .nav-divider
                td
                  | Add this class to a 
                  code= "<li>"
                  |  element to create a divider separating menu items.
          p
            span.badge NOTE
            | You can also add subtitles to nav items. Just create a 
            code= "<div>"
            |  element inside the 
            code= "<a>"
            |  element within the list item.
          
          .preview-box
            .width-per-33
              ul.nav.nav-side(data-nav='')
                li.nav-header Header
                li
                  a(href='')
                    | Item
                    div Subtitle
                li
                  a(href='') Item
                li.nav-divider
                li
                  a(href='') Item
          
          hr
          
          h2 Style modifiers
          p
            | There are several modifiers to style the nav according to the context, 
            | in which it is used.

          h3 Nav side

          p
            | Add the 
            code .nav-side
            |  class to place a nav inside your sidebar, panels or anywhere else in your content.
          
